Description: =================================
        Muctr_System_Core
        =================================
        
        MAKE CHNAGES
        ------------------------------
        
        To change those package, you need:
        
        1. clone this repo
        
        2. make changes
        
        3. use python setup.py bdist --formats=zip
        
        4. copy stable package to version/<version number>/ directory
        
        5. push changes
        
        6. in instance pip install --upgrade git+https://.... with your version
        
        
        INSTALL
        -------------------------
        
        To intall this package you need:
        
        1. be in muctr system repository
        
        2. Have instance to add in muctr system
        
        3. use pip install git+https://bitbucket.org/muctr_system/muctrsystem_core/src/master/versions/0.7.0.0_stable/muctrsystem_core-0.7.0.0.zip
        
        4. done
        
        
        Quick start
        -------------------------
        
        1. Add "polls" to your INSTALLED_APPS setting like this::
        
            INSTALLED_APPS = [
                ...
                'muctrsystem_core',
            ]
        
        2. Include the polls URLconf in your project urls.py like this::
        
            path('', include('muctrsystem_core.urls', namespace='core')),
        
        3. Run `python manage.py migrate` to create the polls models.
        
        4. Change settings middleware to related non auth systems::
        
            MIDDLEWARE = [
                'django.middleware.security.SecurityMiddleware',
                'django.middleware.common.CommonMiddleware',
                'corsheaders.middleware.CorsMiddleware',
                'django.middleware.clickjacking.XFrameOptionsMiddleware',
                'muctrsystem_core.middlewares.AuthMiddleware',
            ]
        
        6. Change settings rest fraemwork settings::
        
            REST_FRAMEWORK = {
                'DEFAULT_AUTHENTICATION_CLASSES': [
                    'muctrsystem_core.authentication.SessionAuthentication'
        
                ],
        
            }
        
        5. Add settings::
        
            # ----------- MUCTR CORE SETTINGS -----------------------#
        
            # take from apiendpoint
            API_TOKEN = EVARS.INSTANCE_TOKEN
        
            # All registred in api endpoint models
            API_INSTANCE_MODELS = {
              'users': ('User', ),
              'employee': ('Position', 'PositionHeld', 'Worker',)
            }
        
            #all relation proxy models
            API_INSTANCE_DEPENDENCIES = {}
